        </h2>                
    </div>
    <div style="text-align: left; font-size: small;" class="componentDescriptionTxt">
        <p>
            The Aspose.Cells.GridWeb is shipped with a built-in Worksheets Designer. You may
            activate the designer from the Visual Studio IDE. In Visual Studio, right click the
            Grid Control in a webform, then select "Worksheets Designer..." from the popup menu.</p>
        <p>
            With the designer, you can:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Create or remove Custom Command Buttons.</li>
            <li>Set the binding datasource for worksheets. </li>
            <li>Create or remove the binding columns for worksheets. </li>
            <li>Create or remove validations for binding columns. </li>
        </ol>
        <p>
            The designer helps you to improve your development productivity.</p>
